    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<h2>Ostren Pell — The Leak in Caelith's Office</h2>\n<p><em>Early thirties. Audit Hall correspondence clerk for four years; leaking to an unknown handler for two of those four. Recruited via gambling debt (his late father's), kept in place by his unmarried older sister Sera. Drowning. Believes he has no exit.</em></p>\n<h3>Combat behavior</h3>\n<p><strong>None.</strong> Yields immediately. Will physically resist only if the party attempts to harm Sera in front of him; even then he will not attack — he will throw himself in front of her.</p>\n<h3>Statblock summary (CR 0, PB +2)</h3>\n<p>AC 10 · HP 9 (2d8) · Speed 30 ft. · Init +0 · Passive Perception 11</p>\n<p>STR 9 · DEX 11 · CON 10 · INT 14 · WIS 12 · CHA 10. Skills: Insight +3, Investigation +4.</p>\n<p>Languages: Common, Old Aerdi (reads), Yeomanry diplomatic cipher (writes).</p>\n<h3>Source</h3>\n<p><em>Blooming Rot, Part 2 — Phase 5.</em> See <em>Phase 5 — Loftwick NPCs → Ostren Pell</em> for full profile and the five-choice handling system.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
